I drive for medical appointments. I drove an elderly lady who had a stroke and later developed extreme pain in both legs. The daughter told me the doctors kept sending her back to the care center and brushed off her complaints of leg pain. The daughter continued to press the doctors until they finally ran tests and discovered the clots. By then she had to have her leg amputated but the surgeon told the daughter she would die during surgery. He told the daughter that they could administer a lethal dose of morphine and end her suffering. The doctor told the daughter that her mother was a burden and would be better off dead. The daughter asked him if he meant to put her down like a sick animal and he said yes. She told him he better not and he better make sure her mother didn't die. She called the police and nothing was done. She has a lawyer and her mother is doing well. It is happening in a whole lot of ways.
